No one is even sure who Pol Pot actually was, his appearance changed over the years, he might have been multiple people, his pseudonym meant "Politique Potentiel" (Potential Policy), in the Khmer Rouge politicians were referred to as numbers, e.g. "Number One", "Number Four" etc.

Dmitry Galkovsky's explanation that he just served as a cover of some global elite group to do a nation-level experiment on mass psychological control and terror and serve as a warning to what they can do to others makes more sense than literally any remotely normal explanation.

It's so insanely ridiculous that people just have to treat it as a joke instead of actual recent history. A guy with an empty, unknown biography named Potential Policy creates a Hell on earth as a communist totalitarian state and genocides millions in a genuinely bizarre fashion.

Just found out that one of the Khmer Rogue's biggest open supporters in Europe, Birgitta Dahl, a Swedish SocDem Minister of Energy (lol) and Minister of The Environment and in the 2010s a UNICEF chairwoman, who denied the ongoing genocide in the 70s croaked just a few days ago...
